This paper deals with differential privacy, which is a concept commonly used in database research (cs.DB). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for finding the best strategy for computing multiple correlated aggregates, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the optimization problem, which involves numerical methods and optimization techniques commonly used in computer science (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR).
